{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d4f08f8-64f3-4fc3-8362-8130ab6248d0","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch test`**.\n\n- `dotnet test` runs tests once and exits; no hot reload.\n- `dotnet run` is for running apps, not test projects.\n- **`dotnet watch test`** watches for file changes and automatically re-runs your tests, giving you the hot-reload workflow for a test project.\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nThis will recompile and re-run your tests whenever you save a change.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6e538e7f-e379-40b0-8128-3ff3112da559","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to use hot reload with .NET testing. Let me look at their project to understand the context better.","outputTokens":160,"requestId":"3404:1BDA61:B7A13D:D764EA:69F40564"},"id":"d0b4de05-fd7a-448f-9d75-ae52be81d093","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:44:10.315Z","parentId":"d4ed3d53-2944-478a-bffe-41b1fd11c95e"}
